<SECOND>PM-BRF--Buggy Accident,0106</SECOND>
<HEAD>Amish Buggy Driver Charged in Traffic Accident; Horse Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BIRD IN HAND, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Amish buggy driver was given a
traffic citation after his horse collided with a car and had to be
destroyed, police said.
   Isaiah Glick, 52, of Lancaster, was cited Wednesday for making a
left turn into the path of the car, said East Lampeter police
Officer Robert Reed.
   The car struck Glick's horse, which went crashing through the
windshield, demolishing the car, police said.
   The horse had to be humanely destroyed.
   The car driver was treated for cuts. Glick was not injured.
