<HEAD>DC-9 Slides Off Runway at Chicago's Midway Airport</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A DC-9 jetliner with 35 people aboard skidded off
a runway after landing at Midway Airport during a light snow
shower, officials said. No injuries were reported.
   Midway Airlines Flight 116 from Dallas slid about 100 feet off
the end of the runway late Wednesday, said a duty officer at the
Federal Aviation Administration who declined to give his name.
   ``The airplane is still upright _ on airport property in the
grass,'' said Lisa Howard, a spokeswoman for the city's Department
of Aviation.
   The passengers had no problem getting off the plane using the
regular stairs and were taken to an airport lounge, Midway Airlines
spokeswoman Sandra Allen said.
   She said the airplane was slightly damaged.
