<HEAD>Reward Offered For Suspect Who Spent Day in Court</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A murder suspect who was in court this week on
a traffic matter is now being listed as the city's most wanted
fugitive and police are offering $10,000 for information leading to
his arrest.
   Police sought the public's help Wednesday in finding Shelton C.
Watkins, 17, who is wanted in connection with two homicides in the
District of Columbia. He has also been charged with murder and rape
