not do your homework?'' said his mother, Gwendolyn Battle.
   Police spokesman Lt. Reginald Smith said Watkins was not
arrested during his court appearances Tuesday because the warrants
for his arrest were issued late Tuesday, after his time in court.
   District police were still seeking Watkins late Wednesday.
   Ralph Weinstein, whose bonding company posted a $15,000 bond on
behalf of Watkins in October for an unrelated case, said Watkins
was in court Tuesday for a traffic matter and a juvenile matter.
