<HEAD>11-Month-Old Summoned For Jury Duty</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSFIELD, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Tyler Morey got a jury summons this
week, but he won't be appearing in court for quite some time.
That's because his mother won't let the 11-month-old go out alone.
   The baby got his notice in the mail on Monday, his mother,
Heather Barnes, said today. She said she went to Superior Court and
``told them he wasn't going to make it. They sent me 10 different
places and everybody laughed at me.''
   The error finally was straightened out.
   ``He's excused,'' a court spokeswoman said today. ``He's under
18 and not above 70.'' Court officials blamed the error on a
computer glitch.
   Barnes said she considered waiting until the summons date of
Feb. 5 and then showing up in court with the baby.
   ``But then I decided they'd probably be mad,'' she said.
