<FIRST>r i AM-Mangano 1stLd-Writethru a0589 12-14 0264</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Mangano, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0589,0269</SECOND>
<HEAD>Actress Silvana Mangano in Coma in Madrid</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: UPDATES throughout with more on her condition, background, CORRECTS
spelling of de Laurentiis, sted de Laurentis, and Mastroianni, sted Mastroiani.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MADRID, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Italian actress Silvana Mangano was
hospitalized in a coma and was near death, a doctor said Thursday.
   Mangano, 59, had entered Luz Hospital on Monday and underwent
surgery for a tumor between her lungs, said Dr. Antonio Aguado,
chief of the intensive care unit.
   ``There is no hope that her condition will improve,'' he said,
adding that she was ``near clinical death.''
   The tumor had left Mangano unable to digest food, a condition
that forced doctors to perform surgery. He did not say how long she
had been in a coma.
   Her three daughters were in Madrid to be with her, Spanish
National Radio reported. A son died in an air crash in Alaska in
1981.
   Mangano gained fame for her acting in 1940s and 1950s
neo-realist Italian films.
   She portrayed a sensual country girl in the 1948 film ``Bitter
Rice.''
   Italian film director Giuseppe De Santis cast her in the part
after she had won the Miss Rome beauty contest and began playing
supporting roles in post World War II films.
   In 1949, she married Dino de Laurentiis, the producer of
``Bitter Rice.'' They separated in 1983.
   She worked with the most prestigious Italian film directors,
including Vittorio de Sica, Pier Paolo Pasolini, Mario Monicelli
and Luchino Visconti.
   In her most recent work, she appeared alongside Marcello
Mastroianni in the film ``Dark Eyes.''
</TEXT>
