<HEAD>Ethnic Albanians Clash with Yugoslav Police</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BELGRADE, Yugoslavia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   About 400 ethnic Albanians clashed
with police Thursday night in the Kosovo town of Pec, denouncing
Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic and demanding release of
former Kosovo leader Azem Vlasi, Tanjug news agency reported.
   The protesters hurled stones at security personnel as they
marched through the streets before police dispersed them and took
four Albanians into custody.
   The incident was prompted by a change of street names in the
