enacted last spring that effectively curtailed the autonomy of
Kosovo, one of two provinces of Serbia, the largest Yugoslav
republic.
   Vlasi, Kosovo's former communist leader, is on trial in Titova
Mitrovica on counterrevolutionary charges. He was accused of
inspiring a weeklong miners' strike and riots in the province in
which at least 25 people died.
   Vlasi said his trial was politically motivated.
   Sporadic battles with riot police, now regularly posted in the
streets, have become commonplace in the province.
