<SECOND>AM-BRF--Yellowstone Visits,0139</SECOND>
<HEAD>Yellowstone Visits for 11 Months Top Full-Year Attendance Record</HEAD>
<DATELINE>YELLOWSTONE NATIONAL PARK, Wyo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yellowstone National
Park, finishing its first full year since it was swept by wildfires
in 1987, drew more tourists during the first 11 months than in any
previous full year, park statistics show.
   Park spokeswoman Marsha Karle said 2,660,346 visitors entered
the park between Jan. 1 and Nov. 30, toppling the 1978 tourism
record of 2,623,141 for 12 months.
   The number of tourists will continue to grow this month.
Yellowstone's winter season begins Friday, when facilities open at
Old Faithful and park roads open to snowmobiles. The Mammoth Hotel
near Gardiner opens Dec. 21.
   A total of 899,259 vehicles were logged in the park this year,
compared to 749,539 in 1988 and 880,545 in 1987, park statistics
show.
</TEXT>
