<HEAD>Son of Crooner Died of Self-Inflicted Gunshot Wound To Head</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lindsay Crosby, a son of the late crooner
Bing Crosby, died of a self-inflicted gunshot wound to the head,
the county coroner's office confirmed Wednesday.
   The report supported earlier conclusions that Crosby, 51, had
committed suicide Monday at a Calabasas condominium where he was
staying while undergoing treatment for alcoholism.
   Coroner's Deputy Claude Boucher confirmed the cause-of-death
finding from Crosby's autopsy.
   A family friend said the suicide came after Crosby learned his
inheritance had run out. Assembled 45 years ago, it was based on
investments in crude oil, a market that has softened considerably
in the past few years.
   Lindsay Crosby, who lived with his wife, Susan, and two of his
four sons in suburban Sherman Oaks, was the youngest of the four
brothers born to Bing and Dixie Lee Crosby.
