   The stock market churned ahead in erratic yearend trading
Wednesday, as the Dow Jones average of 30 industrials closed with
an 8.96-point gain at 2,761.09. Bond prices were mostly higher.
   The dollar finished mixed in New York trading against other
major currencies after rebounding overseas.
   Gold futures prices fell sharply as did futures prices of silver
and platinum; heating oil rose for the 11th straight day; livestock
and meat futures advanced; and grains and soybeans were mostly
higher.
