   Here are sales results for the eight major U.S.
automakers for first period of December 1989.
   Percentage changes in sales are based on average daily sales
during each period rather than comparisons of straight totals.
There were eight selling days in the period this year and nine
selling days last year, and 289 selling days so far this year
compared with 291 selling days in the corresponding period a year
ago.
   Cars and trucks made in the United States by Honda, Nissan,
Toyota, Mazda and Mitsubishi are counted as domestic and appear in
this table. Subaru and Isuzu began producing cars and light trucks
in September at a joint venture plant in Lafayette, Ind.
