<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Unemployment     12-14 0109</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Unemployment,0116</SECOND>
<HEAD>Jobless Rate Falls to 5.8 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Britain's unemployment rate fell 0.1 percent to
5.8 percent in November, its lowest level since the autumn of 1980,
the government said Thursday.
   The jobless rate, which registered 5.9 percent in October, has
been falling for 40 months.
   The seasonally adjusted rate stood at 7.5 percent in November
1988, the Department of Employment said.
   The number of jobless fell by 25,200 in November, more than the
20,000 the financial markets had been expecting.
   Without seasonal adjustment, the number of unemployed totaled
1.61 million in November, compared with 1.64 million in October and
2.07 million a year ago.
