<FIRST>r f BC-Earns-GeneralMills     12-14 0198</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Earns-General Mills,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>Reports Record Second-quarter Earnings</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Mills Inc. reported record
second-quarter earnings Thursday, a 24.3 percent gain over the year
earlier that the company attributed to strength in its food and
restaurant businesses.
   The company said it earned $91.4 million or $1.11 a share for
the three months ended Nov. 26, vs. $73.5 million or 96 cents a
share in the comparable 1988 quarter.
   For the first half of its fiscal year, the company reported
earnings of $206.3 million, compared with $297.3 million last year.
Earnings per share for the first half were $2.50, compared with
$3.62 in the 1988 period.
   Sales for the second quarter this year grew 16 percent to $1.6
billion and, for the first six months, increased 14 percent to $3.1
billion.
   ``Our results to date keep us well on the path toward another
year of record sales, earnings and earnings per share,'' said
Chairman Bruce Atwater.
   Restaurants led General Mills' strong second-quarter operating
performance with increases in sales and operating profits of 18
percent and 40 percent, respectively.
   Consumer Foods' second-quarter gains in sales and operating
profits were 16 percent and 13 percent, respectively, the company
said.
</TEXT>
