<SECOND>BC-Auto Prodn,0153</SECOND>
<HEAD>Up This Week</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: Only version planned.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Domestic automakers were scheduled to produce
223,124 cars and light trucks this week, up from last week's
215,143, Ward's Automotive Reports said Thursday.
   This week's production is lower than the same week a year ago,
when 260,816 cars and light trucks were produced, the trade journal
said.
   U.S. automakers were scheduled to make 146,160 cars this week,
compared with 129,088 a week ago and 168,519 in the same week in
1988.
   Light truck production for the week was scheduled at 76,964,
compared with last week's 86,055 and last year's 92,297.
   Canadian automakers were to build 27,153 cars this week, up from
24,446 a week ago and from last year's 18,380.
   Canadian light truck production was scheduled at 21,048,
compared with 20,840 a week ago and 21,547 in the same week last
year.
